@node Installation "Autocrop: Installation"

                                  Installation
                                 --------------

- copy the file Autocrop.pss from drawer plugins2/ to ArtEffect:plugins2/

- copy Autocrop.guide whereever you can retrieve it.

After the next start of ArtEffect2+ the menuentry "Autocrop VR..." should be
available in Menu Filter/Other.

@endnode

@node Requirements "Autocrop: Requirements"

                                  Requirements
                                 --------------

- the only thing you need is ArtEffect2+

@endnode

@node Usage "Autocrop: Usage"

                                     Usage
                                    -------

   The usage is quite easy, after calling the plugin via menu, you will see a
   little window. Please note that I'm using 'mask' as synonym for 'stencil'
   in ArtEffect.

   Cropcolor: Selects the corner of the picture from where the cropcolor should
              be taken.


   Tolerance: Selects the tolerance of the cropcolor. Everything within the
              given range is assumed as cropcolor and therefore cropped.
              A tolerance of 0 is done with an optimized version of the picture
              scanner so it is faster than with any tolerance set.


   Mode: There are three different modes

      Autocrop: Just crops anything that is assumed to be cropcoloronly.

                Cropping doesn't respect the current masking, it only respects
                the colorchannels. The mask is cropped as the picture is.


      Generate Mask: Does just the same as Autocrop, but doesn't crop the
                     picture. It just generates a mask over the border that
                     would be cropped. The mask is added to any existing mask.
                     The operation is always done with the complete picture,
                     it is NOT restricted to the unmasked area.

                     "Show Stencil" is not automatically enabled and in some
                     rare cases it may be necessary to disable and then reenable
                     "Show Stencil" to let ArtEffect show the mask, but this is
                     true for any other maskmanipulating operation in ArtEffect.

               Note: In contrast to ArtEffect2 ArtEffect3 does not save the
                     mask before doing a plugin operation.  So if a plugin
                     changes the mask, this operation is not undoable in
                     Arteffect3. 

      Maskcrop: Crops the picture to the biggest rectangular that is not
                entirely masked. 


@endnode

@node Notes "Autocrop: Notes"

                                     Notes
                                    -------


 - Autocrop was written on an Amiga 4000 with Cyberstorm MK1 060 and compiled with
   SAS/C 6.58.

 - There seems to be a problem in ArtEffect and so it is not working on
   unmasked areas with a height of 1 pixel ... not my fault

 - This PlugIn has no AREXX-Interface and is not localized nor the documentation
   is avaiable in any other language than english (or whatever this is here).
   That may or may not change in the future.

 - If you are interested in getting the information how long an operation took
   try this: setenv VRPLUGINTIMING 1



@endnode

